    </author>
    <content>&lt;P&gt;I have created an app with SAP Build Apps with Google Firebase as backend.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;I use it to create events that contain a date field with the data type "Date/Time Text".&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;In Google Firebase I have selected what I think is the correct data type "Timestamp".&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;Now to the problem: When I test the app with the preview app on my iPhone, everything works correctly -&amp;gt; I create a data set and this is correctly created as a timestamp in Firebase.&lt;BR /&gt;But when I want to test the app with the WebPreview (SAPCloud), the new data record in Firebase is not saved as a timestamp but as a string. Is this a problem with the Web Preview?&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;Thank you in advance for your feedback!&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;Kind regards&lt;BR /&gt;Felix&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;</content>
